This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with improving the memory capacity and time scale of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) using associative memory. Additionally, the paper also focuses on the performance of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are a type of RNN. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

As the paper deals with memory and retrieval tasks, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Finally, the paper also involves computer vision tasks, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
